{
  "texts": [
    "Sequential Recommender SystemIn many online applications, temporal information in users' historical interactions is both valuable and crucial for modeling dynamic preferences and generating accurate recommendations [49].",
    "To leverage this temporal information, Rendle et al. [40] introduced one of the first sequential recommender systems, using a first-order Markov chain to model changing user preferences over time.",
    "With the advancement of deep learning, neural networks have since been widely adopted for sequential recommendation [9].",
    "For example, Jannach et al. [20] utilized gated recurrent units (GRUs) as the backbone to encode user interaction sequences.",
    "However, GRUs suffer from gradient explosion or vanishing problems and can only capture item information in a strictly sequential manner."
  ]
}